usage: seedbank [-h] [--version] {list,pxe,iso,manage,daemon} ...

seedBank - Debian/Ubuntu netboot installations the way it is meant to be...
(c) 2009-2012 Jasper Poppe <jgpoppe@gmail.com>

positional arguments:
  {list,pxe,iso,manage,daemon}
                        commands
    list                list resources like netboot images, seed files, Puppet
                        manifests, configuration overrides, file overlays,
                        pxelinux.cfg files, netboot images and ISOs
    pxe                 manage netboot installations, prepare a pxelinux.cfg
                        file with all the settings required for a netboot
                        installation
    iso                 build an (unattended) installation ISO
    manage              download and manage netboot images, syslinux files and
                        ISOs
    daemon              seedBank daemon

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --version             show program's version number and exit

for more information visit: http://www.infrastructureanywhere.com
